	<h1>Our History</h1>
	<p>
		The Movies and Dramatics Club of SRM University was founded in 2014 by a
		group of passionate students who wanted to create a platform for artistic
		expression and performance. Over the years, the club has grown
		significantly, becoming a central part of the university's cultural life.
	</p>
	<h2>Milestones</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>2014:</strong> Club founded and first production staged.</li>
		<li><strong>2015:</strong>
			First annual theatre festival hosted, attracting participants from various
			universities.</li>
		<li><strong>2017:</strong>
			Collaboration with the Film Club to produce a short film, which won
			several awards.</li>
		<li><strong>2019:</strong>
			Launch of the Summer Acting Workshop series, providing intensive training
			for aspiring actors.</li>
		<li><strong>2020:</strong>
			Adaptation to virtual events and performances during the pandemic,
			maintaining member engagement and community spirit.</li>
		<li><strong>2022:</strong>
			Record-breaking audience attendance for our annual play production.</li>
		<li><strong>2024:</strong>
			Celebrating our 10th anniversary with a grand gala and a year-long series
			of special events.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		Throughout our history, we have remained committed to promoting the
		performing arts and providing a supportive environment for our members to
		develop their talents. We look forward to continuing this tradition and
		creating even more memorable experiences in the years to come.
	</p>
